-- Air China, Chinese Carriers Raise Ticket Prices, Shanghai Daily Reports
-- Bloomberg News
-- 2010-07-28T00:10:28Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-28/air-china-chinese-carriers-raise-ticket-prices-shanghai-daily-reports.html

          
          
             Air China Ltd., China Southern
Airlines Co. and China Eastern Airlines Corp. raised ticket
prices for premium seats this month as business travel demand
improved, the Shanghai Daily reported today, without saying
where it got the information.  
 The carriers increased first-class fares to as high as 2.8
times economy seat prices and business-class to as much as 2
times, according to the newspaper.  
 Previously, first-class fares were about 1.5 times higher,
the report said.  
 To contact the reporter on this story:
Jian Guo Jiang in Shanghai at 
 jjiang@bloomberg.net   
          
          


  


        